<br>
In the new spell list from Luclin, there's a level 54 spell called Jolting Blades which imbues your weapons with a proc that acts like Jolt. Initially i thought it sounded great, but now I'm not so sure.<br>
<br>
The casting time on Jolt is low, and at 51+ I rarely have trouble casting it. Now, if I've snared, nuked and attacked the mob and I'm now at the top of the hate list, a swift, successful Jolt will invariably pop the mob back on the real tank. <br>
<br>
However there are the times when you want to top a mobs hate list, mainly to get it off the cleric/chanter/casters. Last thing I'd want is to get the mob OFF the almost dead cleric just to have this thing proc, drop down hate list, and likely wind up with a cleric_corpse_01.<br>
<br>
Anyone got any opinion? Any ranger out there think this spell has a use, bearing in mind 55+ we have Jolt and Cinder Jolt?<br>
<br>
Cheers,<br>
Mestrick.<br>
<br>
