<br>
Honestly, i agree with Tann (BTW, thx for the help on general Tann for Ticona and Dobber).  It's a situational spell that you'll use now and then.  And before you say "But i said when tying to clear the casters/clerics" .. i think the jist is, if your casters/clerics are under attack, the main tank (or alt tank if there are 2 in the group) should switch mobs to taunt/get aggro off the caster.<br>
<br>
As a cleric, I often chain-stun mobs on my chanter to get aggro.  With 2500+ hp and 900+ AC, i can take a beating and they cant.  Plus I can DB/DA and save myself, they cant.  A paladin will do the same thing too.  Turn to the mob and root/stun it to get it off the caster.<br>
<br>
As a druid, i often chainsnare when i see my chanter under attack.  i much rather die than risk a total wipe out  I always play with Root and Snare up, solo or grouped.<br>
<br>
So,what that means to you is if you've imbued your weapons with this spell, and it's Captain Ranger to the Rescue time, turn off attack, target the mob, press taunt (rangers have taunt, right?) and snare until you get the mob off.  Also, try rooting the mob and telling the caster to move.<br>
<br>
